             deposed, that she was at the former Evidence's that Day, and dined with the Prisoner there. He also Called several to his Reputation, one who said that he was a Plaisterer, and worked for Mr. Weymer in Hatton Garden a Month, used to be paid at his House, and knew no ill of him. The Jury considering the whole matter, found him <rs id="t17210830-51-verdict265" type="verdictDescription">
